
PROGRAM NAME:  Excelsior Phase One: Lysandia
VERSION:       2.0 - Released 4/18/94
PUBLISHER:     Castle Software
               6755 Mira Mesa Blvd. #123-258
               San Diego, CA  92121-4311
CONTACT:       Daniel Berke, Internet address danberke@netcom.com

SYSTEM REQ'S:  IBM PC, XT, AT, PS/2 or compatible with 640k memory.  VGA
               graphics adaptor and a hard drive.

DESCRIPTION:   Excelsior is a computer role-playing-game (RPG) which returns
               players to the classic style of gaming which defined the
               standard in the early '80s.  In Excelsior, you become a
               "fixer" - A demigod with the task of fixing a minor glitch in
               the Lysandian universe.  A chaotic presence has taken control
               of the king and is threatening to disturb the predetermined
               destiny of the planet.  Your task is to identify the chaos and
               destroy it so that Lysandia can be returned to its normal
               course.

RESTRICTIONS AND AUTHORIZATIONS FOR DISK VENDORS:

Excelsior is NOT public domain or "freeware", but is being distributed
as "shareware".

Written permission is not required for distribution of Excelsior as long
as the following conditions are met:

   -  All files supplied by Castle Software on the Excelsior disk(s) are
      included on the vendor's distribution diskette.  These files may
      not be altered.  Files may be added by the vendor which provide
      the user with technical assistance, startup instructions, the
      vendor's name, etc.  No files may be added which contradict
      information in the files supplied by Castle Software.

   -  No more than a modest distribution fee may be charged by the vendor.

   -  In its promotional literature, the vendor explains the nature of
      the fees paid by the customer and the obligations arising from
      continued use of shareware software.

   -  Operators of electronic bulletin board systems are permitted to
      post Excelsior for downloading by their users as long as the above
      conditions are met (if applicable).

   -  All vendors or sysops must inform Castle Software of the inclusion
      of Excelsior in their catalog.  This is done to ensure that the
      vendor or sysop has the latest version of Excelsior.  If a vendor
      produces a catalog, Castle Software requests a copy in order to
      verify the accuracy of any descriptions of Excelsior.

If the above conditions are met, Castle Software grants vendors and sysops
the right to distribute Excelsior as shareware immediately.

